item.description:
@Realm_of_Dark wrote:

I’ve been searching through google for a while… trying to find a Java 6 decompiler, but all the decompilers I have found only work with Java 5 byte code (DJ Decompiler and JD Decompiler). thus, with the 508 HD client I am trying to decompile, several methods produce errors that I don’t know how to fix…

so, here’s my question. if there is some home-brewed java 6 decompiler out there, could someone tell me the download link? OR could someone tell me a tutorial on how to manually decompile something like this:

// 18: invokespecial 366 Class106:method1544 (B)V // 21: aload_0 // 22: sipush 255 // 25: putfield 322 Class106:anInt1793 I // 28: getstatic 320 // 31: iconst_1 // 32: iadd // 33: putstatic 320 // 36: bipush 152

all help is greatly appreciated.[br][br][size=1]Posted on: August 21, 2009, 08:59:08 am[/size][hr]anyone? :eek:
